121
00:06:34,972 --> 00:06:42,518
[SPEAKER_03]: Just to kind of bring you up to speed on where we are and kind of talk a little bit about this change in plans from the MSBA.

122
00:06:43,538 --> 00:06:51,364
[SPEAKER_03]: As you all know, we submitted the preliminary design program report, the PDP, to the MSBA on February 25th.

123
00:06:52,936 --> 00:06:57,780
[SPEAKER_03]: All 29 options were accounted for and documented per the MSBA's guidelines.

124
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:16,556
[SPEAKER_03]: After their initial review, they followed up with us with the project team to acknowledge that while we had met the minimum requirements in their documents, they wanted us, they wanted this committee to narrow the options from 29 options all the way down to three to five no later than April 2nd.

125
00:07:19,338 --> 00:07:28,161
[SPEAKER_03]: So that we could further study fewer options as we move into the PSR, the preferred schematic report phase.

126
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:37,264
[SPEAKER_03]: So while this is all happening between now and hopefully our next meeting, we can get down to those three or five.

127
00:07:37,324 --> 00:07:38,625
[SPEAKER_03]: I'll talk about that in a minute.

128
00:07:39,425 --> 00:07:44,267
[SPEAKER_03]: They are continuing to review our submission to them.

129
00:07:45,628 --> 00:07:54,632
[SPEAKER_03]: They are not waiting for us to do this work to start reviewing those thousand plus page document, which is good news on our end.

130
00:07:55,672 --> 00:08:06,317
[SPEAKER_03]: So this is part of what is considered on our end as a normal back and forth with every MSBA submission.

131
00:08:08,418 --> 00:08:15,083
[SPEAKER_03]: each project is really different, it gets different feedback at this stage, and even as we move forward through the project.

132
00:08:17,045 --> 00:08:23,550
[SPEAKER_03]: As an example of another project that had a lot of, well actually we had 30

133
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:33,720
[SPEAKER_03]: options on another project, we wound up that SBC decided to take a few options off the table ahead of submitting PDP.

134
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:42,729
[SPEAKER_03]: We submitted PDP and their guidance at that stage was to add back the options that had been taken off the table prior to submitting PDP.

135
00:08:45,151 --> 00:08:46,612
[SPEAKER_03]: Every project is different.

136
00:08:46,832 --> 00:08:55,158
[SPEAKER_03]: Every project gets put through a different lens based on complexities, based on the project, based on why there are the number of options there are.

137
00:08:55,279 --> 00:09:02,564
[SPEAKER_03]: So while this, I'm sure, is a frustrating turn to be

138
00:09:05,232 --> 00:09:08,735
[SPEAKER_03]: you know, recommended or requested from the MSBA to us.

139
00:09:10,437 --> 00:09:17,925
[SPEAKER_03]: We are looking forward to, you know, being able to provide more information sooner on fewer options.

140
00:09:18,285 --> 00:09:27,454
[SPEAKER_03]: So that I think is the plus side of this moving forward in a more expedited timeline.

141
00:09:29,015 --> 00:09:41,679
[SPEAKER_03]: While MSBU's guidelines take us most of the way, there is certainly project specific feedback that we hear on each project and this downshift to narrow options quickly has been ours.

142
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:50,762
[SPEAKER_03]: And I do want to say that the project team really does appreciate your shift to expedite this timeline to line up with their request.

143
00:09:52,723 --> 00:10:06,773
